==Galician==
===Etymology 1===
Probably from {{der|gl|pro|jostar||to joust}}.<ref>Cf. {{R:gl:DDGM|justar}}.</ref>
====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|gl|/ˈʃɔstɾa̝/|/ˈʃostɾa̝/}}
====Noun====
{{gl-noun|f}}
# [[flexible]] [[twig]] or [[stick]]
# [[strap]], [[twisted]] stick used for binding
=====Synonyms=====
* {{sense|twig}} {{l|gl|bestrega}}, {{l|gl|fustriga}}, {{l|gl|verga}}
=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|gl|xóstrega||flexible twig}}
===Etymology 2===
From {{der|gl|VL.|*substrare||to set a layer}}, from {{m|la|substratus}}.<ref>{{R:es:DCECH|jostra}}.</ref> Cognate of {{cog|es|jostra}} and {{cog|fro|sostre}}.
====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|gl|/ˈʃɔstɾa̝/|/ˈʃostɾa̝/}}
====Noun====
{{gl-noun|f}}
# leather [[sole]]
# animal [[sickness]]
